fields.description:
As requested (CRUC-1304):

{quote}
* existing createReview* should automatically set reviewers if they are provided by the client. Currently we need many calls to achieve this simple thing
{quote}

Could be established by passing a DetailedReviewData to createReview().

Steps to Reproduce:
# Get ready with a sample binary tars file (e.g. http://www.mirrorgeek.com/apache.org/httpd/httpd-2.2.11.tar.gz).
# Run a checksum on this file:
{noformat}
md5sum --check httpd-2.2.11.tar.gz.md5
{noformat}
# The output result is:
{noformat}
httpd-2.2.11.tar.gz: OK
{noformat}
# Upload this file into a crucible review (goto review > Manage Files > Upload)
# Download this uploaded file into local disk with different location. (goto review > Review > httpd-2.2.11.tar.gz > View File)
# Run a checksum on this downloaded file.
# The output result is:
{noformat}
httpd-2.2.11.tar.gz: FAILED
md5sum: WARNING: 1 of 1 computed checksum did NOT match
{noformat}

Also, the original file & downloaded file has different in file properties, such as size, compression rate, etc.
